import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Mean: {data["age"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'Median: {data["age"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x="height_bins", y="height", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.axhline(y=data['height'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Average Height: {:.2f}'.format(data['height'].mean()))
    plt.xlabel('Height Bins')
    plt.ylabel('Height')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['height_bins'] = pd.Categorical(data['height_bins'], categories=data['height_bins'].unique())
    data = data.groupby('height_bins').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    plt.pie(data['counts'], labels=data['height_bins'], autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, counterclock=False)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of individuals across different height bins?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['height_bins'] = pd.cut(data['height'], bins=[0, 60, 65, 70, 75, 80, 85, 90, 95, 100, 105, 110, 115, 120, 125, 130, 135, 140, 145, 150, 155, 160, 165, 170, 175, 180, 185, 190, 195, 200])
    age_height_bins = data.groupby(['height_bins'])['age'].value_counts(normalize=True).unstack()
    age_height_bins.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age across different height bins?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Height Bins')
    plt.ylabel('Age Distribution')
    plt.legend(title='Age', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
